00:57:25.346 --> 00:57:30.765
I know what to get from them.'I looked at him and said, 'I know.

00:57:30.766 --> 00:57:33.244
I've been there concerning certain things and business deals.

00:57:33.245 --> 00:57:40.319
I understand what you're saying, but not us.'But not us, right?

00:57:40.320 --> 00:57:45.986
We're the salt. We're the light. And the world sees it on us. And as He is, so are we in this world.

00:57:45.987 --> 00:57:55.519
I say it over myself all the time: that light would shine on our face and the world would say, 'There's something different about them.

00:57:55.520 --> 00:58:00.519
There's something different. They have a peace that I'm not familiar with.

00:58:00.520 --> 00:58:06.451
They have a joy that I'm not familiar with. They walk in a marriage—their marriage is good.

00:58:06.452 --> 00:58:11.074
Their children are healthy. Their children are obedient, and they've got a light on them.

00:58:11.075 --> 00:58:16.957
They're not normal teenagers.'I'm not familiar with the level of success.

00:58:16.958 --> 00:58:25.159
I remember what Pastor Chip said about Jack Nicklaus looking at Tiger Woods while he was out there playing golf.

00:58:25.160 --> 00:58:37.679
Pastor Chip said Jack Nicklaus said as they interviewed him, 'What do you think about Tiger Woods?'and he said Jack Nicklaus was one of the greatest, and he looked over and said, 'I'm not familiar with the success.

00:58:37.680 --> 00:58:53.319
I've never seen that before. I'm not familiar with that. I'm not familiar with the level of success that Tiger Woods is operating in right now.'Jack Nicklaus said it, and I thought when he said it, it challenged me: why not you?

00:58:53.320 --> 00:59:05.079
Why not me? Why not us? The world looks and says, 'I'm not familiar with the success that they're walking in.'They're blessed.

00:59:05.080 --> 00:59:08.919
There are people who are blessed. There are people who walk in blessing.

00:59:08.920 --> 00:59:14.910
There are people who walk in health. You know what? I've never seen a family get along like that.

00:59:14.911 --> 00:59:22.879
There's peace when I go around them, and you see them in Walmart or whatever; there's just a peace that flows through them.

00:59:22.880 --> 00:59:26.759
I'm really not familiar with that, but I want to know about it.

00:59:26.760 --> 00:59:30.701
I want to know about what's on the inside. How do they do that?

00:59:30.702 --> 00:59:38.119
How are they successful? How do they always win? I want to be a winner.

00:59:38.120 --> 00:59:44.377
I don't want a participation trophy. I want the first-place trophy.

00:59:44.378 --> 00:59:53.395
I love that we're in it to win it, to be the head and not the tail, above and not beneath.

00:59:53.396 --> 01:00:02.558
And that's why I think prayer that is effective is a winning prayer. It's not a whining prayer. You're a believing believer.

01:00:02.559 --> 01:00:11.771
God is able to do through you exceedingly, abundantly, above all that you dare ask or think, according to the power that works in you.

01:00:11.772 --> 01:00:22.619
And you're a believing believer. I'm not a doubter. I'm a believer, and I'm an overcomer by the blood of the Lamb and by the word of my testimony.

01:00:22.620 --> 01:00:31.231
You either believe it or you don't. I'm not a victim. I'm a victor. That's what the Lord told me.

01:00:31.233 --> 01:00:38.381
He said, 'Braden, you can't be a victim and go on the glory side and the victory side.

01:00:38.382 --> 01:00:50.719
A victim doesn't walk on the victory side.''Well, I've had all this.'The Lord said, 'Brandon, who hasn't had a story?

01:00:50.720 --> 01:00:56.462
Everybody has a story. Everybody's had something hard they've been through in their life. You're not anything different.

01:00:56.463 --> 01:01:07.759
Yeah, you have a child that's overcome special needs, and you've got a child that's overcoming autism, and you've got this stuff going on, but there's somebody else with a worse story than you.

01:01:07.760 --> 01:01:19.119
And you can either camp around your sad pity party and how you feel sorry for yourself, but you can look across the street and see somebody that has it a lot worse.

01:01:19.120 --> 01:01:29.283
And there's always somebody that's overcoming something different than you are.'But I refuse to be a victim and not a victor.

01:01:29.284 --> 01:01:43.319
The ones that get the job done are the ones that have that bulldog faith and say, 'I refuse.'As the Lord was driving around today, He said, 'You've got to practice like a champion.

01:01:43.320 --> 01:01:55.039
You've got to believe.'What did Michael Jordan do, in his natural ability, to practice to be a winner?

01:01:55.040 --> 01:01:59.239
You've got to think this is the major leagues. That's what He said to me.

01:01:59.240 --> 01:02:07.919
'You've got to think this is the major leagues. You can't think in the minor leagues. This isn't college level anymore.

01:02:07.920 --> 01:02:12.359
You've got to think and train like a champion.'That's what Pastor Chip would even tell us.

01:02:12.360 --> 01:02:21.239
You've got to think and train like a champion. You can't be thinking the way you're thinking anymore, worried about whatever.

01:02:21.240 --> 01:02:26.239
What did Michael Jordan do to get where he is? What did Derek Jeter do? What did John Elway do?

01:02:26.240 --> 01:02:34.279
What did Troy Aikman, Michael Irvin, or Emmitt Smith, the greats, do to get where they were?

01:02:34.280 --> 01:02:41.479
Did they sit and feel sorry for themselves? No, they acted, and they had a swag that was successful.

01:02:41.480 --> 01:02:48.959
After they got to the NFL, after they got to these places, they didn't still act like they did in college.

01:02:48.960 --> 01:02:53.635
They didn't act like they did in high school. You go from glory to glory.

01:02:53.636 --> 01:02:59.519
And the only way I can tell you all this, maybe, is to bring it to a natural level for you: sports.

01:02:59.520 --> 01:03:06.999
I love sports. But you go from glory to glory to glory to glory.

01:03:07.000 --> 01:03:13.279
And the way you are in the pros is not the way you're going to act when you were in high school.

01:03:13.280 --> 01:03:19.319
You've got to carry yourself differently. You're a victor.

01:03:19.320 --> 01:03:25.280
You're a champion. You've got to train like a champion. You've got to act like it.

01:03:25.281 --> 01:03:29.735
And I'm just trying to help stir you up so you don't have that victim mentality.

01:03:29.736 --> 01:03:49.879
Because if you have a victim mentality, you're never going to have a winner's mentality, and you're never going to be able to take over things and say, 'Listen, I've got the ring.'You know, like Pastor Chip; he has that old championship ring on his finger that he got from the Astros when he was a scout.

01:03:49.880 --> 01:04:01.799
It's a different mentality. So, I want to stretch you to believe bigger, to stretch yourself to think bigger.

01:04:01.800 --> 01:04:07.616
You've got to think bigger in these last days and not have that victim mentality.

01:04:07.617 --> 01:04:10.379
The Lord corrects me all the time because sometimes I feel sorry for myself.

01:04:10.380 --> 01:04:19.959
No, stop that! I've created you for more than that. Go back to the fundamentals.

01:04:19.960 --> 01:04:24.375
Go back to the basics of Christianity. Go back to when you're having a hard day.

01:04:24.376 --> 01:04:27.158
'How did you get here in the first place, Brandon?'Spending time with Me.

01:04:27.159 --> 01:04:36.489
That was all about the friendship sermon that I told you last time. Go back to the basics.

01:04:36.490 --> 01:04:43.710
Don't forget the fundamentals: reading your Bible, praying in the spirit, and fellowship with Me, singing songs.

01:04:43.711 --> 01:04:50.171
Go back to the ABCs. When you're a goose in the fog, it's like training in war.

01:04:50.172 --> 01:04:58.358
They repeat it until it's in that muscle memory. They just act.

01:04:58.359 --> 01:05:06.599
The moment something happens in war, they don't freeze because it's so grounded in them; it's just their muscle memory.

01:05:06.600 --> 01:05:15.846
Remember that doctor at the prayer conference? He said most wrecks always happen within a couple miles of the house because you're on autopilot.

01:05:15.847 --> 01:05:19.319
You don't think; you can just go there without even thinking.

01:05:19.320 --> 01:05:23.248
You don't even realize what street you're turning down a lot of times because you can be thinking about something else.

01:05:23.249 --> 01:05:30.666
And because you have muscle memory—you've done it so many times—your mind doesn't even have to really process within a couple miles of your house.

01:05:30.668 --> 01:05:38.083
You can just go there with your eyes closed, basically, because your mind already knows which way it's going to go before you even do it, because it's muscle memory.

01:05:38.084 --> 01:05:42.620
Just like that. That is grounded in you, and that's why we have to be with the word.

01:05:42.621 --> 01:05:47.653
It's just in us; you react immediately. What did you say about first response?

01:05:47.654 --> 01:05:55.599
What was your first response whenever he hurt his finger? When you do these things, what's your first response?

01:05:55.600 --> 01:06:02.399
The moment you come into trouble, what's your first response?

01:06:02.400 --> 01:06:08.599
Regardless of what you're going through, your first response matters. Your first response matters.

01:06:08.600 --> 01:06:15.269
It's not dropping a bad word or yelling at your kids, your wife, or your dog.

01:06:15.270 --> 01:06:21.390
What's your first response? The word. It's in you. It's muscle memory.

01:06:21.391 --> 01:06:27.483
What comes out of you out of the abundance of your heart? The mouth speaks.

01:06:27.484 --> 01:06:42.719
What's in abundance in your heart? Out of the abundance of your heart, the mouth speaks. What's your first response?

01:06:42.720 --> 01:06:50.103
If it's blankety-blank, if it's this or that, then you don't have enough muscle memory.

01:06:50.104 --> 01:06:54.849
You know, the word needs to become more of a priority in your life because of the abundance of your heart.

01:06:54.850 --> 01:07:05.119
What's in the overflow? And I challenge myself; I'm speaking to myself. It's not you. Brandon messes up.

01:07:05.120 --> 01:07:09.759
I dropped something on my toe the other day with the air conditioner guy there, and I'm sure he heard me because I said a bad word.

01:07:09.760 --> 01:07:17.168
I'm just being real with you. And my son looked at me and he goes—I went, 'Well, there is overflow crud.

01:07:17.169 --> 01:07:26.759
Something I've got to work on. The old man came out of that coffin too quick.'I'm not proud of it, just being real.

01:07:26.760 --> 01:07:32.119
And it's embarrassing. You go, 'Well, that was embarrassing. You haven't been in the word enough.

01:07:32.120 --> 01:07:37.289
The first reaction shouldn't have been that after you dropped that thing on your toe,'and I did.

01:07:37.290 --> 01:07:49.074
It hurt. So, it's just being real. But we're all a work in progress, and I just tell you that because you need to hear it.

01:07:49.075 --> 01:07:56.319
